title: President of Kyrgyzstan - Wikipedia
snippet: Almazbek Atambayev was peacefully succeeded by Sooronbay Jeenbekov in 2017. However, Jeenbekov resigned from office due to the 2020 Kyrgyzstani protests and was succeeded by Sadyr Japarov. indicates an individual serving as an acting or provisional president of Kyrgyzstan

title: IFES Election Guide | Elections: Kyrgyz Presidency 2017 General
snippet: The last presidential election in Kyrgyzstan occurred on October 30, 2011. President Almazbek ATAMBAEV was elected president in the first round with 63.2% of the vote.
